# Atlas — Build Log

Project: Atlas — minimal NVIDIA-only OpenAI/Anthropic-compatible API proxy
Target: ~/claude/atlas (port 8788)
Reference (read-only): ~/api_maker (KeyHive, port 8787 — UNTOUCHED, still running)

---

## Goal

Extract the working NVIDIA proxy logic from KeyHive into a clean, standalone
project named Atlas. KeyHive stays frozen on 8787. Atlas runs on 8788.
The two coexist with zero shared state.

---

## Architecture decisions

- **One provider, no router.** KeyHive's `FallbackManager` (HF↔NVIDIA arbiter)
  is gone. With a single provider there is nothing to arbitrate — NVIDIA is
  called directly.
- **`/v1/messages` bug fix.** KeyHive hardcoded the Anthropic endpoint to HF
  (`keyhive_proxy.py:379`), so it never reached NVIDIA. Atlas routes
  `/v1/messages` to NVIDIA directly. This is the whole point of the proxy.
- **Env prefix `ATLAS_`.** No `KEYHIVE_` vars anywhere. Separate stats dir,
  separate keys file, separate venv.
- **Key store upgrade.** KeyHive's `NvidiaKeyStore` rotated blindly — a burned
  `nvapi-` key retried every cycle. Atlas's `NvidiaKeyStore` adds per-key
  cooldown: a key that 429/401/403/5xx is skipped for 30s instead of hammering
  it. This is the one place logic was added, not copied.
- **Stats schema collapsed.** KeyHive's `provider_hf`/`provider_nvidia` split
  is gone — single `provider_nvidia` counter. `record_*(provider, ...)` keeps
  the `provider` arg for call-site compatibility but no longer branches.
- **Port 8788.** Hardcoded in: service file, `atlas_proxy.py` default,
  `bin/atlas` default, installer `.env`/shell-rc wiring. Never 8787.

---

## Files written

### Verbatim-extracted (logic copied, comments/env cleaned)
- proxy/__init__.py            — package marker
- proxy/openai_compat.py       — OpenAI↔Anthropic↔router JSON translation (verbatim)
- proxy/stats.py               — per-request stats (ATLAS_STATS_DIR, single-provider schema)
- proxy/system_prompt.py       — system-reminder strip + override injection (verbatim)
- proxy/nvidia_client.py       — NVIDIA httpx client (verbatim from fallback/nvidia_client.py)

### Rewritten / new
- proxy/nvidia_key_store.py    — round-robin pool + per-key cooldown (from fallback/key_store.py + upgrade)
- proxy/atlas_proxy.py         — FastAPI app, NVIDIA-only, no HF/FallbackManager (from keyhive_proxy.py)
- bin/atlas                    — CLI: start|stop|restart|status|logs (clean, ~132 lines)
- systemd/atlas-proxy.service  — port 8788, WorkingDirectory /root/claude/atlas, ATLAS_ env only
- setup/requirements.txt       — httpx, python-dotenv, fastapi, uvicorn[standard], rich
- setup/install.sh             — venv + pip bootstrap (no node/npm)
- setup/installer.py           — systemd install + CLI symlink + Claude env wiring (8788)
- ARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md         — the pre-build audit/plan

### Seeded by agent (pending final confirmation)
- data/keys.txt                — 6 NVIDIA nvapi- keys (from KeyHive's nvda_fallback_keys.txt)
- data/system_prompt_override.txt — operator override (verbatim copy)
- data/proxy_stats.json        — fresh empty stats
- data/.gitkeep
- .gitignore                   — ignores venv, .env, keys.txt, stats, plugin cruft
- README.md                    — Atlas NVIDIA-only docs

